review_blob: Decent eurotrash. Better than usual mainstreams. Good beer for sauna and/or summerday.
Pours black with decent beige head. Bready, malty aroma with hints of caramel. Malty, sweet taste. Little bit too sweet for me.

Crazy beer. Smooth, bready aroma. Dark brown with small beige head. Breast taste with super smooth feeling in mouth. Never thought that I will rate any beer without lots of hops that highly. Or was it just long day?

Bottle. Pours copperish orange with white head. Aroma - well well well. Sweet, bready, hoppy and some herbs as well. Taste is at the start sweet and then hops kick in. Its really bitter and aftertaste lasts almost forever in its bitterness. This beer is not for weak people. Its monstruos!
Pours amber with white head. The head lasts for a while. Hoppy, malty, sweet aroma with some citrus in it. Nice bitter, mouthdrying aftertaste.
Light copper with a white head. Sweeitsh aroma - also yeast and malts in it. Decent beer - nothing too special, but better than usual eurolager.
Pours amber with a large white head which disappears quite quickly. Pine, citrus and fruits in aroma. Medium carbonation - so easy to drink. Nice bitter aftertaste.

Pours golden/light copper with a small white head. In aroma theres alcohol with hints of orange and hops dominating other aromas. Tastes sweet with alcohol hints with a nice bitter aftertaste. Really smooth beer to drink.
Pour hazy orange with a lot of white head. Malty, fruity aroma. Little bit sour taste. Nice beer for a warm day.

Pours dark amber - light brown with a small white head - looks really great in the glass. In aroma - watery sweet malts. Taste surprises a little bit - it even does not feel too sweet at the start - then I realize - its the palate. Its light bodied, but somehow creamy with soft carbonation. Something I really like to have in the beers. Taste itself is still too sweet for me and the beer itself boring.
Pours hazy golden yellow with a big white head. Aroma - malts, yeast, flowers and some citrus. Sweet taste.
Pours golden with white head. In aroma - hops, fruits, some sweet flowery notes as well. Nice bitterness and not as sweet as the aroma tells you.
Pours light copper/amber with white head. In aroma - pine, citrus and some sweet notes (honey). Little sweet, but bitter aftertaste helps. Nice beer.
Pours golden with a white head. Aroma is sweet, malty, hoppy. Some citrus in it (as it should be considered what hops were used). Citrus, fruits and bitter finish in taste.
Nice beer. Dark golden with a white head. Aroma - piney, citrus and some sweet malts. Tastes good, bitter and with nice lasting aftertaste.
Disappointment. Malt dominates. Not comparable to regular IPA. Decent beer, but should not called IPA. Might be that this is what IPA used to be - but now ....
Nice amber with small white head. In aroma hops, citrus, some pine and maybe also some grassy hints. Tastes good! Really good! Some caramel in taste with nice hoppy and bittery aftertaste.
Decent German pilsner. Aroma is like the most big-brewery-mass-production-beers are having. Taste is surprisingly fresh and nice.
Aroma is sweet, malty and fruity. Tastes sweet. Moderate bitterness in the finish.
Eurolager, but kind of a good one. Nothing much in aroma - malt, hops and hints of caramel. Malty taste turns out to a nice little bit bitter finish.
Hazy pale yellow with a small white head which disappears almost instantly. In aroma - hops, grass, hay, citrus, fruits. Nice bitterness in taste. Nice light pale ale.
Another eurolager. Watery, not hoppy, not malty liquid. Nothing special at all.
Hazy golden. Small white head. In aroma yeast, caramel, herbs and some alcohol. Prepares you for a sweet beer. Actually not as sweet as one would think. Kind of good beer.
Pours hazy amber with a small beige head. Malts, caramel, spice in aroma. Some sweetness and also alcohol in taste. Not entirely my cup of tea.
Corny, malty, hoppy waterlike beer. Nothing special - probably nice drink for sauna.
Pours clody yellow with a white head. Fruity, hoppy sweet aroma with hints of honey. Nice bitter aftertaste.
beer_name: To l Ridiculously Close To Sanity

review_blob: Hazy reddish brown with a small beige head. In aroma malts, bread, hops and some dried plums. Dry bitter aftertaste.
Light brown or dark yellow with a small head. Nice hoppy and malty aroma with hints of citrus. Taste is sweet, but also nicely bitter.
Foggy orange with small white head. Aroma of citrus, orange, hops. Really fresh aroma. Taste is the same plus some malt and grass notes. Nice bitter aftertaste. Nice beer.
Dark brown with a small beige head. Coffee, roasted malts, chocolate and fruits in aroma. Little bit too sweet for my taste
beer_name: Brewfist / Prairie Artisan Ales Spaghetti Western

review_blob: Hazy golden with white head. In aroma - citrus, hops, malts. Some sweetness with nice bitter aftertaste. I would like to have another one ;)
beer_name: Brewfist / Beer Here Caterpillar Pale Ale

review_blob: Dark brown with a beige head. Aroma - pine, hops, blueberries and some roast as well. Taste is good, Hoppy, piney and bitter with some hints of berries. Really good beer!

Strangely low rating for Phjala, but I really did not like it. It was bitter, but I was hoping some more fruity hints out of it. Hazy light golden with a white head which disappears really quickly. Nice and hoppy aroma - some hints of fruits in the aroma which are not present at the taste (at least not for me).
Foggy light brown with a beige head. Not too much carbonation. Citrus, hops, malt and honey? in aroma. Nice bitter taste with lasting aftertaste. Good beer.

Bottle from Brewdog Glasgow. Reddish-copper with almost no (white) head. In aroma, which is really intense, malt, caramel, wood, alcohol, fruits, spices and ofcourse some hops. One of the craziest aromas IMHO. Nice and smooth, but tooooo sweet.
Ruby, beige head. Malts, caramel in aroma. Sweet malts in taste. Decent beer - not that sweet as most of the Lithuanian beers.
Normal porter. Nothing much to say about this except that its a little bit too sweet for my taste.
I call them all eurolagers. Nothing special. Just a yellow thing in your glass.
I call them all eurolagers. Nothing special. Just a yellow thing in your glass.
I call them all eurolagers. Nothing special. Just a yellow thing in your glass.
Pours cloudy orange with a small white head. Aroma is really nice - pine, citrus, fruity. In taste grapefruit with a nice bitterness. Dry mouth feeling with a nice bitter aftertaste. Really nice IPA.
Pours light brown with white, almost nonexisting, top. In the smell - lots of bready malts with some grassy notes. Taste - sweet, sweet, too sweet. Some bread in aftertaste.

Pours foggy amber. White top disappears quickly. In aroma sour bread and malts. Tastes sweet, even too sweet. Aftertaste its sweet as well. One good thing is smoothness of the palette which brings the score over 2.
Pours orange and foggy. Small white head. Fruits, citrus and my favorite - hops in aroma. Nice grapefruit in taste. Somewhat watery finish takes off some points.

Oh well. Pours golden-yellow with medium white head. Head disappears immediately. In aroma - well theres nothing to say - dishwashing cloth smell with nothing else. Tastes as smells - nothing to say - mainstream eurolager. Not sure its even deserves name beer.
Pours cloudy yellow with a nice white head. Spices, yeast, malts and maybe some citrus in aroma. Tastes like usual belgian beer: malty, little bit sweet and some peppery notes. Decent beer.

Strange beer. More like a sparkling wine than a beer. Pour nice golden with a white head. Yeast, sugar in aroma. Also hints of malt, spices and hops in the nose. Tastes like - not sure - 50% of champagne with a 50% of a nice hoppy beer. Cool!

Dark brown (red color hints as well) with a tan head. Herbs, vanilla, dark chocolate in aroma. Tastes heavy - some chocolate sweetness, roasted malts and nice bitter finish. I wish Ive had a cellar to age it some 10-15 years.

Pour foggy brown with a white head. Little bit of a dishwashing cloth aroma with some fruits and hops with it. Taste is nice - hoppy with some sweet fruity taste. Nice beer - could be more hoppy I would say.
Golden with a medium, no lasting, white head. Aroma - hoppy, fruity and grassy. A litte bit citrus in taste as well. Nice beer. Nice hoppy bittery finish.
